item.title: How do i code on other peoples servers
item.dc:creator: @Javacisnotrecognized _^_
item.description:
@Javacisnotrecognized wrote:

Client is the thing you see. It records what key buttons you push, and what mouse clicks you click, and then sends it to the server. The server then figures out what the clicks and presses translate into, and sends the response to your client.

The client then takes the servers response, and puts it in a form that looks like what it is supposed to look like.
